{"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"sink","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each closure is initially created in a “floating” state, which means"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that the initial reference count is not owned by any caller."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function checks to see if the object is still floating, and if so,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"unsets the floating state and decreases the reference count. If the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"closure is not floating, ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_closure_sink()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" does nothing."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The reason for the existence of the floating state is to prevent"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"cumbersome code sequences like:"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"(C Language Example):","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["closure = g_cclosure_new (cb_func, cb_data);","g_source_set_closure (source, closure);","g_closure_unref (closure); \/\/ GObject doesn't really need this"],"syntax":"C"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Because ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_source_set_closure()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (and similar functions) take ownership of the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"initial reference count, if it is unowned, we instead can write:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"(C Language Example):"}]},{"syntax":"C","type":"codeListing","code":["g_source_set_closure (source, g_cclosure_new (cb_func, cb_data));"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Generally, this function is used together with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_closure_ref()"},{"text":". An example","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"of storing a closure for later notification looks like:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"(C Language Example):"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"C","code":["static GClosure *notify_closure = NULL;","void","foo_notify_set_closure (GClosure *closure)","{","  if (notify_closure)","    g_closure_unref (notify_closure);","  notify_closure = closure;","  if (notify_closure)","    {","      g_closure_ref (notify_closure);","      g_closure_sink (notify_closure);","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Because ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_closure_sink()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" may decrement the reference count of a closure","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"(if it hasn’t been called on ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"closure"},{"type":"text","text":" yet) just like "},{"code":"g_closure_unref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_closure_ref()"},{"type":"text","text":" should be called prior to this function."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef\/sink()"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Takes over the initial ownership of a closure."}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/closureref\/sink()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","extendedModule":"GLibObject","title":"sink()","externalID":"s:10GLibObject15ClosureProtocolPAAE4sinkyyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:10GLibObject10ClosureRefV","symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"sink","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef\/ClosureProtocol-Implementations"]]},"references":{"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/ClosureRef/sink()":{"role":"symbol","title":"sink()","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"sink","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/closureref\/sink()","abstract":[{"text":"Takes over the initial ownership of a closure.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef\/sink()"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/ClosureRef":{"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GClosure"},{"type":"text","text":" represents a callback supplied by the programmer."}],"url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/closureref","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ClosureRef","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","title":"ClosureRef","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"ClosureRef"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject":{"abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","title":"GLibObject","role":"collection","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/ClosureRef/ClosureProtocol-Implementations":{"abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef\/ClosureProtocol-Implementations","title":"ClosureProtocol Implementations","role":"collectionGroup","kind":"article","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/closureref\/closureprotocol-implementations"}}}